This is the story of a devastated man whose wife, he says, has been quarrelling him all the time. The worst part is that the same wife even ends up beating him up in the presence of their children. Given Kenya is an African society which expects a man to be stronger, many men go through domestic violence at the hands of their wives but remain mum over the issue for fear of been ridiculed in the society. The African society expects a man to be strong and head of the family. But this man has persevered for long and has opened up. How should he handle the situation?